        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[codex] add centralized agent spend controls",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- add centralized monthly spend caps with reserve-before-request and settle-after-response accounting\n- add versioned model pricing, conservative token-cost estimation, cache and long-context rates, and fail-closed handling for unpriced usage\n- support native and compatibility routing for Codex and Claude Code with agent, session, project, and client attribution\n- meter JSON and streaming responses and expose provider/model usage through the admin console\n- document deployment, client configuration, pricing manifests, and enforcement boundaries\n\n## Why\n\nOrganizations need one policy and analytics layer across agent clients and model providers. Enforcing budgets in ClawRouter keeps the control plane server-side, supports centrally managed accounts, and prevents a local macOS utility from becoming the enforcement boundary.\n\n## Impact\n\nAdministrators can assign policy-level monthly budgets and inspect usage centrally. Budgeted traffic is reserved before reaching the provider, then reconciled against reported usage. Requests that cannot be safely priced require an explicit fixed request price.\n\nHard caps apply only to traffic routed through ClawRouter; direct provider traffic remains outside the gateway's authority.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `cargo test --workspace` — 158 tests passed\n- `pnpm test:scripts` — 34 tests passed\n- `pnpm --dir admin test` — 9 tests passed\n- `pnpm --dir admin build`\n- `cargo build -p clawrouter-edge --target wasm32-unknown-unknown`\n- browser smoke test of the Usage dashboard\n- independent autoreview: clean\n- `git diff --check`\n",
